Global Telepsychiatry Market Insights
Telepsychiatry Market size was valued at USD 5.3 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 17.3 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 18.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Telepsychiatry Market Overview
The global telepsychiatry market was valued at approximately USD 2.3 billion in 2024 and is expected to reach around USD 9.6 billion by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 19.6% from 2025 to 2032. This rapid growth is driven by an increased demand for accessible mental health services, technological advancements, and government initiatives promoting telemedicine. The market’s expansion is further accelerated by the growing awareness of mental health and a rising preference for remote healthcare services. North America currently dominates the telepsychiatry market due to the high adoption of advanced technologies and an increasing number of mental health patients seeking online consultations.

